I"¹	<p>Welcome to the <b>R</b>obotics and <b>I</b>ntelligent <b>S</b>yst<b>E</b>ms Laboratory (<b>RISE</b>) at Arizona State University! We work on design and control of advanced robotic systems, including wearable assistive robots, soft robots, and unmanned aerial vehicles. Our aim is to design novel structures/mechanisms and intelligent learning/control algorithms for robots to safely and efficiently collaborate with human in dynamic tasks. 
We are part of <a href="https://msn.engineering.asu.edu/">School of Manufacturing Systems and Networks</a> at the <a href="https://engineering.asu.edu/">Ira A. Fulton Schools of Engineering</a>. We are affiliated with the <a href="https://robotics.asu.edu/">ASU Robotics Group</a> and <a href="https://globalsecurity.asu.edu/center-human-artificial-intelligence-and-robot-teaming">Center for Human, Artificial Intelligence, and Robot Teaming (CHART)</a>. The lab is directed by Dr. Wenlong Zhang, an Associate Professor of Systems Engineering at Arizona State University.</p>
